# Unity C# Style

- Use `PascalCase` for types/methods/properties.
- Use `_camelCase` for private fields.
- Keep methods short; one behavior per method.
- Prefer explicit types unless `var` improves readability.
- Use `nameof(...)` for parameter/argument exceptions.

# Unity Safety

- Cache component references in `Awake`/`Start`; avoid repeated `GetComponent`.
- Do not allocate in hot paths (`Update`, `FixedUpdate`) when avoidable.
- Use `[SerializeField] private` instead of public mutable fields.

# Example

```csharp
// BAD
public Rigidbody2D rb;

// GOOD
[SerializeField] private Rigidbody2D _rb;
```
